An analysis of Governor Gavin Newsoms tweeting habits

Gavin Newsom is Californias first social media governor. He has the distinction of being the most followed U.S. governor on Twitter by a lot.

So we decided to learn more about Newsoms tweeting habits.

We used a Twitter API to collect tweets from all U.S. governors accounts, official and personal, between March 1 and December 31, 2019. This is as far back as we could go using the API and still analyze a complete set of governors tweets. We were able to collect older tweets going back to January 1, 2017 for Gavin Newsoms personal account.

We studied Governor Newsoms tweeting habitshow he tweets between his two accounts and compared to other U.S. Governors. Heres what we found:

Newsoms tweeting habits

Newsom tweets from two accounts: an official account, @CAgovernor, and a personal account, @GavinNewsom.

We graphed the number of tweets he posted each month from each of his accounts. After becoming governor, he started tweeting more from his official account.

However, when it come to tweeting about President Trump, Newsom favors his personal account.

Gavin Newsom also tweets more frequently about Trump from his personal account.

From 02/01/2019 to the end of 12/31/2019, Gavin Newsom tweeted 58 times about Trump from his official @CAgovernor account and 156 times from his personal @GavinNewsom account. He tweeted 1,921 times from his official account and 1,190 times from his personal account in that same time period. In other words, 3% of tweets from his official account mention Trump, compared to 13% of tweets from his personal account, in this 11-month period.

How does Gavin Newsoms Twitter habits compare to other U.S. governors?

For this analysis, we looked at a 10-month time period between 03-01-2019 and 12-31-2019, which is as far back as we could go using the Twitter API and still gather a full set of data for all U.S. govenors.

We looked at which governor tweeted the most from an official or personal account. In this time period, Gavin Newsom ranked 8th in number of tweets from his official account and the 14th from his personal account.

If we only compared which official governors accounts tweeted the most, Gavin Newsom moves into 7th place.

And if we looked at which governor tweeted the most overall (ie. by counting tweets from their official and personal accounts), Newsom becomes the second most prolific governor on Twitter in this time period.

Now lets look at which governor tweeted the most about Trump (or mentions Trump) in this same time period.

If we looked at which governor tweeted the most about Trump (or mentions Trump) from an official or personal account, Gavin Newsom from his personal account ranks third in tweets that mention or are about Trump.
